li.p:
As seen in the graph above: v' is positive whenever v is increasing;
v' is negative whenever v is decreasing;
v' is zero whenever v is constant.

Central difference: to estimate g'(a), we can use

  g'(a) \approx \frac{g(a+h)-g(a-h)}{2h}

for an appropriate choice of h.

At the moment t = 30,
the temperature of the potato is 251 degrees;
its temperature is rising at a rate of 3.85 degrees per minute;
and the rate at which the temperature is rising is falling
at a rate of 0.119 degrees per minute per minute.
